    • Constructor Detail

      • Records

        public Records()
        This is a non-parameterized constructor of Records file which is used to instantiate the FileWriters object. And create bankrecords.txt file. Throws IOException.

    • Method Detail

      • averageCalculation

        public static void averageCalculation()
        This method is used to call Average Comparator and sort the fields based on the Region and Income. This method further sorts the data according to INNER_CITY,TOWN,SUBURBAN and RURAL, sums up the income and takes an average based on the region. This method writes the calculated average into bankrecords.txt File.

      • MinimumMaximum

        public static void MinimumMaximum()
        This method is used to call Region Comparator and sort the fields based on the Income. This method is used to filter the data based on the Region, Minimum and Maximum Income Value. This method writes the minimum and maximum value into bankrecords.txt File.

      • femaleComparator

        public void femaleComparator()
        This method is used to call Female Comparator and sort the fields based on their Sex and Mortgage. This method is used to filter the data based on the Sex, Mortgage and whether they Saving Account. This method writes the count of females in bankrecords.txt File.

      • maleComparators

        public static void maleComparators()
        This method is used to call Male Comparator and sort the fields based on the Sex and car. This method is used to filter the data based on the Number on childern they have (i.e 1). This method writes the count of Male into bankrecords.txt File.

      • closeFile

        public static void closeFile()
        This method is used to close the filewriter.
